name: The Internet Time Machine
tag_list: trends, analytics, parsing, niche, niche-products, fads
overview: The Internet Time Machine software studies world wide supply demand curves to find out what people are looking for “search demand” and compares it to supply “think Google results”. The service downloads over 55,000,000 sources worldwide everyday to find trends and ideas that are growing but don’t have enough organic or PPC results. It is able to spot new trends and products weeks before any other service in the world. Its software runs on the search engine NowRelevant.com and allows for full intergration into corporate platforms.
